init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the “Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The problem with this is that the side effects of the medication are not discovered until it is too late.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The story is told through the eyes of the main character, a 28 year old man who is one of the “Lost Generations."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The story is told in a very poetic way and is very easy to read.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is a very interesting story that will keep you on the edge of your seat.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The story is very well written and the author does a great job of making you feel like you are actually there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is a great story that will make you think about the possibilities of something like this happening in the future.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: Whenever something is thought-provoking it is always beneficial to the consumer as we need to think about these things now and in the future.
